text.section:
Pursuant to this chapter, a judgment creditor of an unincorporated nonprofit association shall not levy execution against the assets of a member to satisfy a judgment based on a claim against the association unless:
A judgment based on the same claim has been obtained against the association and a writ of execution on the judgment has been returned unsatisfied in whole or in part;
The association is a debtor in bankruptcy;
The member has agreed that the creditor need not exhaust association assets; or
Liability is imposed on the member by law or contract independent of the existence of the association.
